acceptBid(address,uint256).details: Accept the bid on the token.

params._originContract: address of the contract storing the token.

bid(uint256,address,uint256).details: Bids on the token, replacing the bid if the bid is higher than the current bid. You cannot bid on a token you already own.

params._newBidAmount: uint256 value in wei to bid.
params._originContract: address of the contract storing the token.

buy(address,uint256).details: Purchases the token if it is for sale.

params._originContract: address of the contract storing the token.

cancelBid(address,uint256).details: Cancel the bid on the token.

params._originContract: address of the contract storing the token.

currentBidDetailsOfToken(address,uint256.details: Function to get current bid and bidder of a token.

getRoleAdmin(bytes32).details: Returns the admin role that controls `role`. See {grantRole} and {revokeRole}. To change a role's admin, use {_setRoleAdmin}.

getRoleMember(bytes32,uint256).details: Returns one of the accounts that have `role`. `index` must be a value between 0 and {getRoleMemberCount}, non-inclusive. Role bearers are not sorted in any particular way, and their ordering may change at any point. WARNING: When using {getRoleMember} and {getRoleMemberCount}, make sure you perform all queries on the same block. See the following https://forum.openzeppelin.com/t/iterating-over-elements-on-enumerableset-in-openzeppelin-contracts/2296[forum post] for more information.

getRoleMemberCount(bytes32).details: Returns the number of accounts that have `role`. Can be used together with {getRoleMember} to enumerate all bearers of a role.

grantRole(bytes32,address).details: Grants `role` to `account`. If `account` had not been already granted `role`, emits a {RoleGranted} event. Requirements: - the caller must have ``role``'s admin role.

initialize(address,address).details: Initializes the contract setting the market settings and creator royalty interfaces.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

payments(address).details: Returns the payments owed to an address.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

renounceRole(bytes32,address).details: Revokes `role` from the calling account. Roles are often managed via {grantRole} and {revokeRole}: this function's purpose is to provide a mechanism for accounts to lose their privileges if they are compromised (such as when a trusted device is misplaced). If the calling account had been granted `role`, emits a {RoleRevoked} event. Requirements: - the caller must be `account`.

revokeRole(bytes32,address).details: Revokes `role` from `account`. If `account` had been granted `role`, emits a {RoleRevoked} event. Requirements: - the caller must have ``role``'s admin role.

safeAcceptBid(address,uint256,uint256).details: Accept the bid on the token with the expected bid amount.

params._amount: uint256 wei amount of the bid
params._originContract: address of the contract storing the token.

safeBuy(address,uint256,uint256).details: Purchase the token with the expected amount. The current token owner must have the marketplace approved.

params._amount: uint256 wei amount expecting to purchase the token for.

setIERC721CreatorRoyalty(address).details: Admin function to set the IERC721CreatorRoyalty. Rules: - only owner - _address != address(0)

setMarketplaceSettings(address).details: Admin function to set the marketplace settings. Rules: - only owner - _address != address(0)

setMinimumBidIncreasePercentage(uint8).details: Admin function to set the minimum bid increase percentage. Rules: - only owner

params._percentage: uint8 to set as the new percentage.

setSalePrice(address,uint256,uint256).details: Set the token for sale. The owner of the token must be the sender and have the marketplace approved.

params._amount: uint256 wei value that the item is for sale
params._originContract: address of the contract storing the token.

tokenPrice(address,uint256).details: Gets the sale price of the token

params._originContract: address of the contract storing the token.

returns._0: uint256 sale price of the token

tokenPriceFeeIncluded(address,uint256).details: Gets the sale price of the token including the marketplace fee.

params._originContract: address of the contract storing the token.

returns._0: uint256 sale price of the token including the fee.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

withdrawPayments(address).details: Withdraw accumulated payments, forwarding all gas to the recipient. Note that _any_ account can call this function, not just the `payee`. This means that contracts unaware of the `PullPayment` protocol can still receive funds this way, by having a separate account call {withdrawPayments}. WARNING: Forwarding all gas opens the door to reentrancy vulnerabilities. Make sure you trust the recipient, or are either following the checks-effects-interactions pattern or using {ReentrancyGuard}.
